{{quote|Section 1. Neither slavery nor involuntary servitude, except as a punishment for crime whereof the party shall have been duly convicted, shall exist within the United States, or any place subject to their jurisdiction.}}

{{quote|Section 2. Congress shall have power to enforce this article by appropriate legislation.<ref>{{cite web|deadurl=no |url=http://www.law.cornell.edu/constitution/constitution.amendmentxiii.html |title=13th Amendment |publisher=Cornell University Law School |work=Legal Information Institute |date=2012-11-20 |accessdate=2013-09-25 |archivedate=2013-09-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901161747/http://www.law.cornell.edu/constitution/amendmentxiii }}</ref>}}

