== 美国奴隶制度 ==
{{Main|美国奴隶制度}}
[[Image:Cicatrices_de_flagellation_sur_un_esclave.jpg|thumb]]

美国建国前的13个北美[[殖民地|殖民地]]都存在奴隶制<ref>{{cite book |title=Law in America: A Short History |last=Friedman |first=Lawrence Meir |year=2004 |publisher=Random House |isbn=9780812972856 |page=69 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=vEyy573xiDIC&pg=PA69&dq=slavery+%22every+colony%22+United+states&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JJTBUeorj9j0BOKggZgO&ved=0CCwQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=slavery%20%22every%20colony%22%20United%20states&f=false |accessdate=2013-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009061053/http://books.google.com/books?id=vEyy573xiDIC&pg=PA69&dq=slavery+%22every+colony%22+United+states&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JJTBUeorj9j0BOKggZgO&ved=0CCwQ6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=slavery%20%22every%20colony%22%20United%20states&f=false |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1787年制订的美国宪法中虽未用到“奴隶制”一词，但包括了多处与其有关的条文。如[[美利坚合众国宪法第一条|第一条]]第二款第3节的五分之三妥协规定众议员名额的分配根据各州“自由人总数加上所有其他人口的五分之三予以确定”，这个“其他人口”就是指奴隶<ref name="USC25-8">{{cite book |title=美国宪政历程：影响美国的25个司法大案 |author=陈伟 |publisher=中国法制出版社 |isbn=7-80182-138-6 |chapter=第八章　引发美国内战的司法判决——斯科特诉桑弗特案(1857) |pages=一、美国宪法暗藏杀机|date=2004年1月}}</ref><ref name="USC25" /><ref name="Li1999" /><ref>{{cite book |author=Jean Allain |title=The Legal Understanding of Slavery: From the Historical to the Contemporary |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=n_KAvAjkEbsC&pg=PA117 |year=2012 |publisher=Oxford University Press |page=117 |access-date=2013-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009060957/http://books.google.com/books?id=n_KAvAjkEbsC&pg=PA117 |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。又如[[美利坚合众国宪法第四条|第四条]]第二款第3节中的{{link-en|劳役逃犯条款|Fugitive Slave Clause}}规定：“根据一州法律须在该州服劳役或劳动的人，如逃往他州，不得因他州的法律或规章而免除此种劳役或劳动”<ref name="USC25" /><ref name="Li1999" />。第一条第九款还规定国会只有在1808年后才能通过立法禁止“任何一州认为得准予入境之人的迁移或入境”<ref name="Foner">{{cite book |last=Foner |first=Eric |title=The Fiery Trial: Abraham Lincoln and American Slavery |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=earytjxi6pEC |accessdate=2013-06-04 |year=2010 |publisher=W. W. Norton |isbn=978-0-393-06618-0 |ref=harv |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009061003/http://books.google.com/books?id=earytjxi6pEC |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|16}}。不过在[[美國憲法第五修正案|第五条修正案]]中有这样的规定：“无论何人……不经正当法律程序，不得被剥夺生命、自由或财产。”<ref name="USC25" /><ref name="Li1999" /><ref>{{cite book|author=Jean Allain|title=The Legal Understanding of Slavery: From the Historical to the Contemporary|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=n_KAvAjkEbsC&pg=PA119|year=2012|publisher=Oxford University Press|pages=119–120|access-date=2013-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009061104/http://books.google.com/books?id=n_KAvAjkEbsC&pg=PA119|archive-date=2013-10-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>废奴主义者用这条修正案来攻击奴隶制，这也是1857年[[斯科特诉桑福德案|斯科特诉桑福德案]]中将奴隶视为财产的法律基础<ref>{{cite book |last=Tsesis |first=Alexander |title=The Thirteenth Amendment and American Freedom: A Legal History |url=https://archive.org/details/thirteenthamendm00tses |location=New York |publisher=New York University Press |year=2004 |isbn=0814782760 |page=[https://archive.org/details/thirteenthamendm00tses/page/n54 14] |quote=Nineteenth century apologists for the expansion of slavery developed a political philosophy that placed property at the pinnacle of personal interests and regarded its protection to be the government's chief purpose. The Fifth Amendment's Just Compensation clause provided the proslavery camp with a bastion for fortifying the peculiar institution against congressional restrictions to its spread westward. Based on this property-rights centered argument, Chief Justice Roger B. Taney, in ''Dred Scott v. Sanford'' (1857), found the Missouri Compromise unconstitutionally violated due process.}}</ref>。[[白人優越主義|白人優越主義]]在当时美国文化上的普遍性也导致无论法律还是实践中奴隶制都获得了支持<ref>{{cite book |last=Tsesis |first=Alexander |title=The Thirteenth Amendment and American Freedom: A Legal History |location=New York |publisher=New York University Press |year=2004 |isbn=0814782760 |pages=18-23 |quote=Constitutional protections of slavery coexisted with an entire culture of oppression. The peculiar institution reached many private aspects of human life, for both whites and blacks. [...] Even free Southern blacks lived in a world so legally constricted by racial domination that it offered only a deceptive shadow of freedom.}}</ref>。

从1777到1804年，所有的北方州都直接或逐步废除了奴隶制，但没有任何一个南方州跟隨，并且其奴隶人口数量还在不断增长，并于1861年达到约400万人的峰值<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|14-16}}。由[[威廉·劳埃德·加里森|威廉·劳埃德·加里森]]等人领导的[[廢奴主義|废奴主义运动]]在北方发展壮大，要求在全国范围内中止奴隶制度，导致南方和北方的关系变得日趋紧张。1836年，联邦众议院制定了反对废奴主义请愿和演讲的{{link-en|堵嘴规则|gag rule}}，试图扼杀[[约翰·昆西·亚当斯|约翰·昆西·亚当斯]]和其他废奴主义众议员的主张。认为不同种族应保持隔离的废奴主义者和担心获得自由的前景会助长奴隶叛乱的奴隶主组成了一个名为[[美国殖民协会|美国殖民协会]]的同盟，他们要求将自由的黑人和奴隶通过移民或殖民的方式送回[[非洲|非洲]]。这一观点得到了包括[[亨利·克莱|亨利·克莱]]在内的多位[[政治家|政治家]]支持，他们担心废奴主义运动会挑起一场[[内战|内战]]<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|20-22}}。1818年和1839年，联邦众议员{{link-en|阿瑟·利弗莫尔|Arthur Livermore}}和约翰·昆西·亚当斯分别提出了淘汰奴隶制的宪法修正案，但都没能赢得足够的支持<ref name="Vile">{{cite encyclopedia |year=2003|title=Thirteenth Amendment |encyclopedia=Encyclopedia of Constitutional Amendments, Proposed Amendments, and Amending Issues: 1789 - 2002 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |editor-first=John R. |editor-last=Vile |pages=449-452}}</ref>。

随着美国的继续扩张，新领土上的奴隶制问题成了国家面临的主要问题。南方州认为奴隶属于财产，因此可以像其它任何一种财产那样从一州移至他州<ref name="Goodwin">{{cite book |last=Goodwin |first=Doris Kearns |title=Team of Rivals: The Political Genius of Abraham Lincoln |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ONhhui9SRsMC |accessdate=2013-09-25 |year=2005 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-0-7432-7075-5 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009040520/http://books.google.com/books?id=ONhhui9SRsMC |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|123}}。1820年的[[密苏里妥协|密苏里妥协]]将[[密苏里州|密苏里州]]接纳为一个蓄奴州，[[缅因州|缅因州]]为一个自由州，由此保持联邦参议院的地区平衡。1846年的一项拨款法案中附加了一个{{link-en|威尔莫特但书|Wilmot Proviso}}，其中规定在所有[[美墨戰爭|美墨戰爭]]中获得的土地上禁止施行奴隶制，这一规定多次经众议院投票通过，但都没能经过参议院这关<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|123}}，之后的[[1850年妥协案|1850年妥协案]]通过接纳作为自由州的[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]暂时化解了这个问题，并设立了一个更强有力的{{link-en|1850年逃奴追缉法|Fugitive Slave Act of 1850|逃奴追缉法}}，禁止在[[哥伦比亚特区|哥伦比亚特区]]进行奴隶贸易，并允许[[新墨西哥州|新墨西哥州]]和[[犹他州|犹他州]]在奴隶制问题上自决<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|59}}。

虽然有上述的折衷方案，但南方和北方的紧张局势在随后的十年中仍继续激化，这其中还受到了其它多方面因素的影响，包括1852年出版的反奴隶制[[小说|小说]]《[[汤姆叔叔的小屋|汤姆叔叔的小屋]]》<ref name="McPherson">{{cite book |last=McPherson |first=James M. |title=Battle Cry of Freedom: The Civil War Era |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=a3nX48n4oeIC |accessdate=2013-09-25 |year=1988 |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-503863-7 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009060544/http://books.google.com/books?id=a3nX48n4oeIC |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|88-91}}，1854年[[堪萨斯州|堪萨斯州]][[堪薩斯內戰|废奴主义势力和支持奴隶制势力的对抗]]<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|146-150}}、1857年[[联邦最高法院|联邦最高法院]]在[[斯科特诉桑弗特案|斯科特诉桑弗特案]]中判定1850年妥协案违宪<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|170-177}}，废奴主义者[[约翰·布朗_(废奴主义者)|约翰·布朗]]于1859年试图在[[哈珀斯费里_(西弗吉尼亚州)|哈珀斯费里]]发起奴隶起义<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|201-206}}以及1860年[[美国总统选举|美国总统选举]]的结果：反对奴隶制的[[共和党_(美国)|共和党人]][[亚伯拉罕·林肯|亚伯拉罕·林肯]]当选成为新的总统。南方各州在林肯当选几个月后宣布脱离联邦，组建[[美利堅聯盟國|美利堅聯盟國]]，并随即挑起了南北战争<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|234-235}}。

== 通过 ==
[[File:James_Mitchell_Ashley_-_Brady-Handy.jpg|thumb]]

1863年1月1日，林肯利用总统战时所拥有的权力颁布了解放奴隸宣言，宣布南方所有叛乱州的奴隶立即恢复自由，但这并没有对那些选择继续效忠联邦的边界州中的奴隶现状产生影响<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|558}}。林肯接着又在1863年12月宣布大赦和重建，承诺只要南方州废除奴隶制，并搜集占其投票人口数10%的效忠誓辞，就给予一个重返联邦的机会<ref name="Vorenberg">{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|47}}。南方州没有轻易接受这个机会，其奴隶制的地位仍不明朗。

在内战的最后几年里，北方联邦的国会议员就多种不同的重建提案进行了辩论<ref name="Vorenberg" />{{rp|48-51}}，其中一些人提出以宪法修正案来在全国范围内永久性地废除奴隶制。1863年12月14日，来自[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]]的联邦众议员[[詹姆斯·米歇尔·阿什利|詹姆斯·米歇尔·阿什利]]提出了一条这样的修正案<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ohiohistorycentral.org/w/Ashley,_James?rec=129 |title=James Ashley |work=Ohio History Central |publisher=Ohio Historical Society |accessdate=2013-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925155528/http://www.ohiohistorycentral.org/w/Ashley,_James?rec=129 |archive-date=2013-09-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[艾奥瓦州|艾奥瓦州]]众议员{{link-en|詹姆斯·F·威尔森|James F. Wilson}}也很快提出了类似的提案。1864年1月11日，密苏里州联邦参议员{{link-en|约翰·B·亨德森|John B. Henderson}}提交了一份废除奴隶制宪法修正案的[[联合决议案|联合决议案]]。由[[伊利诺伊州|伊利诺伊州]]参议员{{link-en|莱曼·特朗布尔|Lyman Trumbull}}担任主席的[[美国参议院司法委员会|参议院司法委员会]]开始将各类相关的不同提议合并成修正案。

由[[马萨诸塞州|马萨诸塞州]]联邦参议员[[查尔斯·萨姆纳|查尔斯·萨姆纳]]和[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]众议员[[撒迪厄斯·史蒂文斯|撒迪厄斯·史蒂文斯]]为代表的{{link-en|激进派共和党人|Radical Republicans}}希望可以通过一条影响更大的修正案<ref name="Tsesis">{{cite book |last=Tsesis |first=Alexander |title=The Thirteenth Amendment and American Freedom: A Legal History |location=New York |publisher=New York University Press |year=2004 |isbn=0814782760}}</ref>{{rp|38-42}}。1864年2月8日，萨姆纳提交了这样一份修正案草案：

<blockquote>“法律面前，人人平等，任何人都不得将他人当做奴隶。国会有权以适当立法来保证美国境内任何地区对此宣言的执行。”<ref name="Stanley">{{cite journal |last1=Amy Dru Stanley |date=2010-06 |title=Instead of Waiting for the Thirteenth Amendment: The War Power, Slave Marriage, and Inviolate Human Rights |journal=American Historical Review |volume=115 |issue=3 }}</ref>{{rp|741-742}}<ref name="SocietyCommission1901">{{cite book |author=Michigan State Historical Society |title=Historical collections |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Yx0zAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA582 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |year=1901 |publisher=Michigan Historical Commission |page=582 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009071536/http://books.google.com/books?id=Yx0zAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA582 |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref></blockquote>

萨姆纳试图绕开特朗布尔控制的司法委员会来增加自己提议修正案获得通过的希望，但没能成功<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=52-53 |quote=Sumner made his intentions clearer on February 8, when he introduced his constitutional amendment to the Senate and asked that it be referred to his new committee. So desperate was he to make his amendment the final version that he challenged the well-accepted custom of sending proposed amendments to the Judiciary Committee. His Republican colleagues would hear nothing of it. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2月10日，司法委员会向参议院提交了一份基于阿什利、威尔森和亨德森草案的修正案<ref>{{cite web|url=http://13thamendment.harpweek.com/hubpages/CommentaryPage.asp?Commentary=05ProposalPassage |deadurl=yes |title=Congressional Proposals and Senate Passage (The Creation of the 13th Amendment) |publisher=''Harpers Weekly'' |accessdate=2013-09-26 |archivedate=2013-01-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130115121319/http://13thamendment.harpweek.com/hubpages/CommentaryPage.asp?Commentary=05ProposalPassage }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=53 |quote=It was no coincidence that Trumbull's announcement came only two days after Sumner had proposed his amendment making all persons 'equal before the law.' The Massachusetts senator had spurred the committee into final action. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

委员会的版本采用了1787年《[[西北條例|西北條例]]》的措辞，该条例当时主要对如今被称为[[美國中西部|美國中西部]]的地区适用，其中规定：“在上述任何地方，奴隶制和强制劳役都不得存在，但作为对于依法判罪的人的犯罪的惩罚除外。”<ref>{{cite journal |last=McAward |first=Jennifer Mason |url=http://www.columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1769-1810.pdf |title=McCulloch and the Thirteenth Amendment |journal=Columbia Law Review |volume=112 |year=2012 |page=1786 |quote=There shall be neither slavery nor involuntary servitude in the said territory, otherwise than in punishment of crimes, whereof the party shall have been duly convicted. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ehZI7PeC?url=http://www.columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1769-1810.pdf |archivedate=2016-01-21 }}</ref>不过，司法委员会采纳亨德森的提议作为新草案基础时也做了一些改动，将其中规定的修正案只需参众两院过半数通过和三分之二的州通过即可生效的规定删除，所以修正案将仍像宪法第五条规定的那样需要两院三分之二多数通过，再由四分之三的州通过<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=54 |quote=Although it made Henderson's amendment the foundation of the final amendment, the committee rejected an article in Henderson's version that allowed the amendment to be adopted by the approval of only a simple majority in Congress and the ratification of only two-thirds of the states. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

联邦参议院于1864年4月8日以38票支持，6票反对通过了修正案。但两个月后联邦众议院的投票结果是93票支持，65票反对，距所需的三分之二多数还差13票，议员投票党派之争非常明显，共和党支持，民主党反对<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|686}}。前[[自由土地党|自由土地党]]候选人[[约翰·C·弗里蒙特|约翰·C·弗里蒙特]]在1864年总统选举中威胁以第三方党派候选人参选反对林肯，不过这一次也站到了支持反奴隶制修正案的立场上。共和党方面虽然有林肯在接受总统候选人提名的信中表示支持修正案，但还是没有形成统一战线<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|624-625}}<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|299}}。弗里蒙特于1864年9月22日退出了选举，转为支持林肯<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|639}}。

===国会辩论===
由于没有南方州代表出席，国会也就没有多少议员从[[道德|道德]]或[[宗教信仰|宗教信仰]]角度来为奴隶制辩护。反对修正案的民主党议员通常是以[[联邦主义|联邦主义]]和{{link-en|州权|States' rights}}为理由展开辩论<ref name="Benedict">{{cite journal |last=Benedict |first=Michael Les |url=http://digitalcommons.law.umaryland.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=3535&context=mlr&sei-redir=1&referer=http%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com.libproxy.usc.edu%2Fscholar%3Fstart%3D40%26q%3Djohnson%2Bthirteenth%2Bamendment%2Bstate%2Bconvention%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0%2C36#search=%22johnson%20thirteenth%20amendment%20state%20convention%22 |title=Constitutional Politics, Constitutional Law, and the Thirteenth Amendment |journal=Maryland Law Review |volume=71 |issue=1 |date=2012-10-31 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |author= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928053319/http://digitalcommons.law.umaryland.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=3535&context=mlr&sei-redir=1&referer=http%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com.libproxy.usc.edu%2Fscholar%3Fstart%3D40%26q%3Djohnson%2Bthirteenth%2Bamendment%2Bstate%2Bconvention%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0%2C36#search=%22johnson%20thirteenth%20amendment%20state%20convention%22 |archive-date=2013-09-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|179}}。一些议员辩称，这样的修正案违背了宪法的精神，已经变成了一场“革命”而不再是一个有效的“修正”了<ref>{{cite journal |last=Benedict |first=Michael Les |url=http://digitalcommons.law.umaryland.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=3535&context=mlr&sei-redir=1&referer=http%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com.libproxy.usc.edu%2Fscholar%3Fstart%3D40%26q%3Djohnson%2Bthirteenth%2Bamendment%2Bstate%2Bconvention%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0%2C36#search=%22johnson%20thirteenth%20amendment%20state%20convention%22 |title=Constitutional Politics, Constitutional Law, and the Thirteenth Amendment |journal=Maryland Law Review |volume=71 |issue=1 |date=2012-10-31 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |pages=179-180 |quote=(Benedict quotes Sen. Garrett Davis:) there is a boundary between the power of revolution and the power of amendment, which the latter, as established in our Constitution, cannot pass; and that if the proposed change is revolutionary it would be null and void, notwithstanding it might be formally adopted. |author= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928053319/http://digitalcommons.law.umaryland.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=3535&context=mlr&sei-redir=1&referer=http%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com.libproxy.usc.edu%2Fscholar%3Fstart%3D40%26q%3Djohnson%2Bthirteenth%2Bamendment%2Bstate%2Bconvention%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0%2C36#search=%22johnson%20thirteenth%20amendment%20state%20convention%22 |archive-date=2013-09-28 |dead-url=no }}Full text of Davis's speech, with comments from others can be found in ''[http://www.archive.org/stream/greatdebatesina17millgoog/greatdebatesina17millgoog_djvu.txt Great Debates in American History] {{Wayback|url=http://www.archive.org/stream/greatdebatesina17millgoog/greatdebatesina17millgoog_djvu.txt |date=20130927182609 }}'' (1918), ed. Marion Mills Miller.</ref>。还有一些反对者警告说，修正案将给予黑人彻底的公民权<ref name="Colbert">{{cite journal |last=Colbert |first=Douglas L. |title=Liberating the Thirteenth Amendment |journal=Harvard Civil Rights – Civil Liberties Law Review |volume=30 |year=1995}}</ref>{{rp|10}}。

共和党议员坚称奴隶制是野蛮的，为了民族进步有必要将之废除<ref name="Benedict" />{{rp|182}}。修正案的支持者还认为奴隶制对白人也存在负面影响，例如由于需要与强制劳役竞争而不得不接受较低的工资水平，以及在南方要求废除奴隶制的白人所遭受的压迫。支持者声称，终结奴隶制可以恢复蓄奴州以审查和恐吓手段所侵犯的[[美国宪法第一修正案|第一修正案]]等多项宪法权利<ref name="Colbert" />{{rp|10}}<ref>{{cite journal |last=TenBroek |first=Jacobus |title=Thirteenth Amendment to the Constitution of the United States: Consummation to Abolition and Key to the Fourteenth Amendment |journal=California Law Review |volume=39 |issue=2 |date=1951-06 |page=180 |quote=It would make it possible for white citizens to exercise their constitutional right under the comity clause to reside in Southern states regardless of their opinions. It would carry out the constitutional declaration "that each citizen of the United States shall have equal privileges in every other state." It would protect citizens in their rights under the First Amendment and comity clause to freedom of speech, freedom of press, freedom of religion and freedom of assembly.}}</ref>。

北方的共和党人和部分民主党人对废除奴隶制的修正案感到激动，并开始就此召开会议并发布决议<ref name="Vorenberg" />{{rp|61}}。许多黑人，特别是南方的黑人，更侧重于把土地所有权和[[教育|教育]]视为解放的关键<ref name="TreleaseXvii">{{cite book |last=Trelease |first=Allen W. |title=White Terror: The Ku Klux Klan Conspiracy and Southern Reconstruction |location=New York |publisher=Harper & Row |year=1971 |page=xvii |quote=Negroes wanted the same freedom that white men enjoyed, with equal prerogatives and opportunities. The educated black minority emphasized civil and political rights more than the masses, who called most of all for land and schools. In an agrarian society, the only kind most of them knew, landownership was associated with freedom, respectability, and the good life. It was almost universally desired by Southern blacks, as it was by landless peasants the world over. Give us our land and we can take care of ourselves, said a group of South Carolina Negroes to a Northern journalist in 1865; without land the old masters can hire us or starve us as they please.}}</ref>。随着奴隶制开始在政治上显得不能成立，北方的民主党人开始逐渐宣布他们对修正案的支持，其中包括[[纽约州|纽约州]]联邦众议员{{link-en|詹姆斯·布鲁克斯|James Brooks (politician)}}<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |page=73 |quote=The first notable convert was Representative James Brooks of New York, who, on the floor of Congress on February 18, 1864, declared that slavery was dying if not already dead, and that his party should stop defending the institution. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[马里兰州|马里兰州]]联邦参议员{{link-en|勒维迪·约翰逊|Reverdy Johnson}}<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |page=74 |quote=The antislavery amendment caught Johnson's eye, however, because it offered an indisputable constitutional solution to the problem of slavery. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>和纽约强大的{{link-en|政治机器|political machine}}[[坦慕尼协会|坦慕尼协会]]<ref name="Vorenberg" />{{rp|203}}。

===国会通过===
[[File:AdoptionOf13thAmendment.jpg|thumb]]
林肯一直担心解放奴隶宣言会遭到推翻，或是在战后失效，因此将宪法修正案视为一个更可靠的解决办法<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|312-314}}<ref>{{cite book |first=David Herbert |last=Donald |title=Lincoln |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fuTY3mxs9awC |accessdate=2013-09-26 |year=1996 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-0-684-82535-9 |page=396 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009074526/http://books.google.com/books?id=fuTY3mxs9awC |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。由于担心从政治上对自己不利，他对外宣称保持中立<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |page=48 |quote=The president worried that an abolition amendment might foul the political waters. The amendments he had recommended in December 1862 had gone nowhere, mainly because they reflected an outdated program of gradual emancipation, which included compensation and colonization. Moreover, Lincoln knew that he did not have to propose amendments because others more devoted to abolition would, especially if he pointed out the vulnerability of existing emancipation legislation. He was also concerned about negative reactions from conservatives, particularly potential new recruits from the Democrats. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不过，林肯在1864年的党纲中提出用宪法修正案来解决废除奴隶制的问题<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sewanee.edu/faculty/willis/Civil_War/documents/republican.html |title=Republican Party Platform, 1864 |author=Willis, John C. |publisher=University of the South |accessdate=2013-09-26 |quote=Resolved, That as slavery was the cause, and now constitutes the strength of this Rebellion, and as it must be, always and everywhere, hostile to the principles of Republican Government, justice and the National safety demand its utter and complete extirpation from the soil of the Republic; and that, while we uphold and maintain the acts and proclamations by which the Government, in its own defense, has aimed a deathblow at this gigantic evil, we are in favor, furthermore, of such an amendment to the Constitution, to be made by the people in conformity with its provisions, as shall terminate and forever prohibit the existence of Slavery within the limits of the jurisdiction of the United States. |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2013-03-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130329015755/http://www.sewanee.edu/faculty/Willis/Civil_War/documents/republican.html }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://rmc.library.cornell.edu/vote/1864/index.html |title=1864: The Civil War Election |publisher=Cornell University |work=Get Out the Vote |year=2004 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |archivedate=2013-06-07 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607064739/http://rmc.library.cornell.edu/vote/1864/index.html |deadurl=no |quote=Despite internal Party conflicts, Republicans rallied around a platform that supported restoration of the Union and the abolition of slavery. }}</ref>。赢得[[1864年美国总统选举|1864年美国总统选举]]后，林肯将第十三条修正案的通过当成自己在立法倡议上的头等大事来抓，于国会还处于“跛脚鸭”时期时开始了他的努力<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|686-687}}<ref name="Vorenberg" />{{rp|176-177, 180}}。民众对修正案的支持率开始攀升，林肯又于12月6日对发表的国情咨文中向国会呼吁，修正案的通过和生效只是时间问题，考虑到所有的因素，这个时间应该是越早越好<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |page=178 |quote=there is only a question of ''time'' as to when the proposed amendment will go to the States for their action. And as it is to so go, at all events, may we not agree that the sooner the better? |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

林肯指示国务卿威廉·H·苏厄德和联邦众议员{{link-en|约翰·B·埃利|John B. Alley}}等人使用任何必要的手段来确保修正案通过，这些手段包括承诺政府公职、政治捐款及传出民主党议员有意改变投票立场的消息等<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|312-313}}<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|687}}。苏厄德有大笔资金直接进行[[贿赂|贿赂]]。重新在众议院提出修正案的阿什利也成功游说了多位民主党议员转为支持<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|687-689}}。众议员赛迪斯·史蒂文斯之后对此评价道：“19世纪最伟大的举措是在美国最纯洁的人的协助和教唆下，利用[[政治腐敗|腐败]]才通过的。”不过，林肯在这场交易中所扮演的确切角色仍然不明<ref>{{cite book |first=David Herbert |last=Donald |title=Lincoln |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fuTY3mxs9awC |accessdate=2013-09-26 |year=1996 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-0-684-82535-9 |page=554 |quote=the greatest measure of the nineteenth century was passed by corruption, aided and abetted by the purest man in America |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009074526/http://books.google.com/books?id=fuTY3mxs9awC |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

由于有民意上的支持，共和党人在1864年的国会两院换届选举中再度获胜，修正案通过的胜算因此进一步加大，议员们声称这毫无疑问是人民的意旨<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=187 |quote=But the clearest sign of the people's voice against slavery, argued amendment supporters, was the recent election. Following Lincoln's lead, Republican representatives like Godlove S. Orth of Indiana claimed that the vote represented a 'popular verdict . . . in unmistakable language' in favor of the amendment. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。反对派则是由1864年民主党副总统候选人，联邦众议员{{link-en|乔治·H·彭德尔顿|George H. Pendleton}}带队<ref name="Goodwin" />{{rp|688}}。共和党则将其要求平等的激烈用词淡化，以求获得更多人的支持<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=191 |quote=The necessity of keeping support for the amendment broad enough to secure its passage created a strange situation. At the moment that Republicans were promoting new, far-reaching legislation for African Americans, they had to keep this legislation detached from the first constitutional amendment dealing exclusively with African American freedom. Republicans thus gave freedom under the antislavery amendment a vague construction: freedom was something more than the absence of chattel slavery but less than absolute equality. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。为了安抚一些批评人士对修正案会造成现有社会结构分裂的担忧，一些共和党人还明确承诺修正案不会对父权体制构成任何不利影响<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=191-192 |quote=One of the most effective methods used by amendment supporters to convey the measure's conservative character was to proclaim the permanence of patriarchal power within the American family in the face of this or ''any'' textual change to the Constitution. In response to Democrats who charged that the antislavery was but the first step in a Republican design to dissolve all of society's foundations, including the hierarchical structure of the family, the Iowa Republican John A. Kasson denied any desire to interfere with 'the rights of a husband to a wife' or 'the right of [a] father to his child. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

1月中旬，[[美国众议院议长|众议院议长]][[斯凯勒·科尔法克斯|斯凯勒·科尔法克斯]]估计修正案距通过还差5票，阿什利于是推迟了表决<ref name="Vorenberg" />{{rp|197-198}}。到了这个节骨眼儿上，林肯强化了对修正案的推动，直接向部分国会议员作出情感性的恳求<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |page=198 |quote=It was at this point that the president wheeled into action on behalf of the Amendment […] Now he became more forceful. To one representative whose brother had died in the war, Lincoln said, 'your brother died to save the Republic from death by the slaveholders' rebellion. I wish you could see it to be your duty to vote for the Constitutional amendment ending slavery. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1865年1月31日，众议院再次对修正案发起表决，各方均未知鹿死谁手。所有的共和党人都投了赞成票，还有16位民主党人也投了赞成票，修正案最终以119票赞成，56票反对获得通过，刚刚超过所需要的三分之二多数<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|313}}。众议院为此爆发了庆祝活动，一些议员当众流下了眼泪<ref name="Foner" />{{rp|314}}。黑人自之前一年开始获许旁听众议院的会议，这天许多前来的人们也在旁听席上欢呼<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|840}}。

1865年2月1日，林肯在修正案上签字，令第十三条修正案成为唯一一条经总统签字并获得通过的[[美国宪法修正案|美国宪法修正案]]，之前[[詹姆斯·布坎南|詹姆斯·布坎南]]于1861年签置的一条支持奴隶制的修正案最终没能在国会通过<ref>{{cite journal |last=Harrison |first=John |title=The Lawfulness of the Reconstruction Amendments |journal=University of Chicago Law Review |volume=68 |issue=2 |url=http://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/1600377?uid=3737800&uid=2&uid=4&sid=21102684005227 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |page=389 |quote=For reasons that have never been entirely clear, the amendment was presented to the President pursuant to Article I, Section 7, of the Constitution, and signed.|date=Spring 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Thorpe |first=Francis Newton |url=http://archive.org/stream/constitutionalh00thorgoog |title=The Constitutional History of the United States, vol. 3: 1861 – 1895 |location=Chicago |publisher=Callaghan |year=1901 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |page=154 |quote=The President signed the joint resolution on the first of February. Somewhat curiously the signing has only one precedent, and that was in spirit and purpose the complete antithesis of the present act. President Buchanan had signed the proposed Amendment of 1861, which would make slavery national and perpetual. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401202642/http://archive.org/stream/constitutionalh00thorgoog |archive-date=2016-04-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。第十三条修正案的存档副本上就带有林肯的签名，位于通常由众议院议长和参议院议长签名的位置下方，在日期的后面<ref>{{cite web |title=Joint Resolution Submitting 13th Amendment to the States; signed by Abraham Lincoln and Congress |work=The Abraham Lincoln Papers at the Library of Congress: Series 3. General Correspondence. 1837-1897 |publisher=Library of Congress |accessdate=2013-09-26 |url=http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=mal&fileName=mal3/436/4361100/malpage.db&recNum=0 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722201222/http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=mal&fileName=mal3%2F436%2F4361100%2Fmalpage.db&recNum=0 |archive-date=2013-07-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2月7日，国会通过决议确认总统的签名是不必要的<ref>{{cite book |last=Thorpe |first=Francis Newton |url=http://archive.org/stream/constitutionalh00thorgoog |title=The Constitutional History of the United States, vol. 3: 1861 – 1895 |location=Chicago |publisher=Callaghan |year=1901 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |page=154 |quote=But many held that the President's signature was not essential to an act of this kind, and, on the fourth of February, Senator Trumbull offered a resolution, which was agreed to three days later, that the approval was not required by the Constitution; "that it was contrary to the early decision of the Senate and of the Supreme Court; and that the negative of the President applying only to the ordinary cases of legislation, he had nothing to do with propositions to amend the Constitution. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401202642/http://archive.org/stream/constitutionalh00thorgoog |archive-date=2016-04-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。林肯共计签置了这条修正案的至少14份纪念性副本，2006年，其中的一份副本以180万[[美元|美元]]的价格成交<ref>{{cite web |author=Tammy Webber |url=http://www.boston.com/news/nation/articles/2011/12/06/lincoln_signed_copy_of_13th_amendment_restored/?page=2 |title=Lincoln-signed copy of 13th Amendment restored |publisher=Boston Globe |work=Associated Press |date=2011-12-06 |access-date=2013-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927212420/http://www.boston.com/news/nation/articles/2011/12/06/lincoln_signed_copy_of_13th_amendment_restored/?page=2 |archive-date=2013-09-27 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 各州批准 ===
[[Image:13th amendment ratification.svg|thumb|400px|right|{{Legend|#0050ff|1865年批准修正案}}
{{legend|#00ff74|在修正案生效颁布后，于1865至1870年批准}}
{{legend|#d500ff|起初驳回修正案，之后于1866至1995年批准}}
{{legend|#b8b8b8|1865年尚不属于美国领地}}]]

修正案送至各州立法部门后，大部分北方的州很快就给予了批准，不过[[特拉华州|特拉华州]]、[[肯塔基州|肯塔基州]]和[[新泽西州|新泽西州]]没有批准，这三个州在1864年的总统大选中也是民主党候选人[[乔治·B·麦克莱伦|乔治·B·麦克莱伦]]获胜。

这个时候战争尚未正式结束，战败南方各州的法律地位仍然模棱两可。不过南方[[路易斯安那州|路易斯安那州]]、[[阿肯色州|阿肯色州]]、弗吉尼亚州和[[田纳西州|田纳西州]]四州重建政府还是批准了修正案<ref name="McPherson" />{{rp|840}}<ref>{{cite journal |last=Harrison |first=John |title=The Lawfulness of the Reconstruction Amendments |journal=University of Chicago Law Review |volume=68 |issue=2 |url=http://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/1600377?uid=3737800&uid=2&uid=4&sid=21102684005227 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |page=390 |quote=Those ratifications raised some tricky questions. Four of them came from organizations purporting to be the legislatures of Virginia, Louisiana, Tennessee, and Arkansas. What about them? How many states were there, how many of them had legally valid legislatures, and if there were fewer legislatures than states, did Article V require ratification by three-fourths of the states or three-fourths of the legally valid state legislatures?|date=Spring 2001}}</ref>。肯塔基州将奴隶制视为对该州战争期间忠于南方邦联的奖励，因此快速而又苦涩地否决了修正案<ref name="Forehand">{{cite journal |last=Forehand |first=Beverly |url=http://digitalcommons.wku.edu/theses/868/ |title=Striking Resemblance: Kentucky, Tennessee, Black Codes and Readjustment, 1865–1866 |publisher=Western Kentucky University |journal=Masters Thesis |date=1996-05-01 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |author= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928114729/http://digitalcommons.wku.edu/theses/868/ |archive-date=2013-09-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{rp|126-127}}。

1865年4月，[[林肯遇刺案|林肯总统被刺杀]]，由于国会正在休会，继任林肯总统职位的[[安德鲁·约翰逊|安德鲁·约翰逊]]开始了一段史称“总统重建”的时期，他亲自监督了[[北卡罗莱纳州|北卡罗莱纳州]]、[[密西西比州|密西西比州]]、[[乔治亚州|乔治亚州]]、[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]、[[阿拉巴马州|阿拉巴马州]]、[[南卡罗莱纳州|南卡罗莱纳州]]和[[佛罗里达州|佛罗里达州]]七个南方州新政府的建立。约翰逊安排自己选中的代表召开政治会议，并极力鼓励他们批准修正案。<ref>{{cite journal |last=Harrison |first=John |title=The Lawfulness of the Reconstruction Amendments |journal=University of Chicago Law Review |volume=68 |issue=2 |url=http://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/1600377?uid=3737800&uid=2&uid=4&sid=21102684005227 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |pages=394-397 |quote=Then came the kicker: The President decided who was loyal, prescribing suffrage qualifications for electing the convention. [...] Pursuant to Johnson's proclamations, the provisional governors organized elections for conventions. Six met in 1865, while Texas's convention did not organize until March 1866. Three leading issues came before the convention: secession itself, the abolition of slavery, and the Confederate war debt.|date=Spring 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Eric L. McKitrick |title=Andrew Johnson and Reconstruction |accessdate=2013-09-26 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=MqL8lmT74HEC&pg=PA178 |year=1960 |publisher=U. Chicago Press |page=178 |isbn=9780195057072 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009074841/http://books.google.com/books?id=MqL8lmT74HEC&pg=PA178 |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |author=Clara Mildred Thompson |title=Reconstruction in Georgia: economic, social, political, 1865-1872 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=i5shAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA156 |year=1915 |publisher=Columbia University Press |page=156 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009074845/http://books.google.com/books?id=i5shAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA156 |archive-date=2013-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>约翰逊希望能在国会12月开会讨论是否重新接纳南方各州之前完成修正案的批准<ref>{{cite book |last=Vorenberg |first=Michael |accessdate=2013-09-25 |url=http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |title=Final Freedom: The Civil War, the Abolition of Slavery, and the Thirteenth Amendment |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2001 |isbn=9781139428002 |pages=227-228 |quote=If, by the time Congress convened in December, the amendment had been ratified with the help of southern states, Johnson's Republican opponents might think twice about denying the southern states their place in the Union. Excluding these states might come at the embarrassing price of nullifying constitutional emancipation. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929034106/http://www.questia.com/read/105900244/final-freedom-the-civil-war-the-abolition-of-slavery |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

南卡罗莱纳和其他各南方州的白人政治家担心国会可能会利用修正案赋予的执法权力授予黑人选举权<ref>{{cite book |authorlink=W·E·B·杜波依斯 |last=DuBois |first=W. E. B. |title=Black Reconstruction: An Essay Toward a History of the Part Which Black Folk Played in the Attempt to Reconstruct Democracy in America, 1860–1880 |location=New York |publisher=Russell & Russell |year=1935 |page=208 |quote=Charles Sumner and others declared that [the enforcement clause] gave Congress power to enfranchise Negroes if such a step was necessary to their freedom. The South took cognizance of this argument.}}</ref>。南卡罗莱纳州批准修正案时发布了其诠释性的声明，称“国会任何企图通过立法改变昔日奴隶政治地位或民事关系之举，都将违背美利坚合众国宪法”<ref>{{cite journal |last=McAward |first=Jennifer Mason |url=http://www.columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1769-1810.pdf |title=McCulloch and the Thirteenth Amendment |journal=Columbia Law Review |volume=112 |year=2012 |pages=1786-1787 |quote=any attempt by Congress toward legislating upon the political status of former slaves, or their civil relations, would be contrary to the Constitution of the United States. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ehZI7PeC?url=http://www.columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1769-1810.pdf |archivedate=2016-01-21 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Thorpe |first=Francis Newton |url=http://archive.org/stream/constitutionalh00thorgoog |title=The Constitutional History of the United States, vol. 3: 1861 – 1895 |location=Chicago |publisher=Callaghan |year=1901 |accessdate=2013-09-26 |page=210 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401202642/http://archive.org/stream/constitutionalh00thorgoog |archive-date=2016-04-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。阿拉巴马州和路易斯安那州也声称他们对修正案的批准并不意味着赋予联邦改变昔日奴隶地位的权力<ref name="McAward">{{cite journal |last=McAward |first=Jennifer Mason |url=http://www.columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1769-1810.pdf |title=McCulloch and the Thirteenth Amendment |journal=Columbia Law Review |volume=112 |year=2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ehZI7PeC?url=http://www.columbialawreview.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1769-1810.pdf |archivedate=2016-01-21 }}</ref><ref name="Tsesis" />{{rp|48}}<ref>{{cite book |last=DuBois |first=W. E. B. |title=Black Reconstruction: An Essay Toward a History of the Part Which Black Folk Played in the Attempt to Reconstruct Democracy in America, 1860–1880 |location=New York |publisher=Russell & Russell |year=1935 |page=208 |quote=(Alabama's exception:) That this amendment to the Constitution of the United States is adopted by the Legislature of Alabama with the understanding that it does not confer upon Congress the power to legislate upon the political status of freedmen in this state.}}</ref>。

